<h1>FreeMathHelp.com's Factoring Calculator</h1>
<h3>Factor Any Expression</h3>
<p>Ready for some extra help factoring algebraic expressions? We're trying =
something new here. FreeMathHelp.com is adding our first AI-powered solver =
tool to assist with learning. We know AI offers some compelling advantages =
with math tutoring in particular - and that doesn't mean just getting answe=
rs blindly. Working through a step-by-step tutoring engine is a great way t=
o practice and solve a tricky problem.</p>
<p>Don't rely on any one tool to do all the work for you, and <strong>alway=
s check your work</strong> for correctness!</p>

<div class=3D"input-group">
    <label for=3D"question">Enter your mathematical expression to factor:</=
label><br>
    <textarea id=3D"question" rows=3D"3" placeholder=3D"E.g., Factor x^2 + =
5x + 6"></textarea>
</div>

<button id=3D"calculateBtn">Factor!</button>

<div id=3D"resultContainer" class=3D"result-container">
    <div id=3D"stepsContainer"></div>
    <div id=3D"progressIndicator" class=3D"progress-indicator"></div>
</div>

<h3>How does it work?</h3>
<p>Enter your problem in the box above and click the button to submit your =
question. Your input should be limited only to common math expressions (see=
 examples below). Please be patient while our AI engine processes your requ=
est. If you're not sure what to enter, look over the sample problems below =
to see the types of expressions this tool can factorise. The solver has bee=
n tweaked specifically to provide step-by-step instruction, not just an ans=
wer. Remember the idea is to *learn* not to copy solutions blindly. As the =
solver matures, this will become more clear as the ability to generate larg=
e numbers of final answers will be restricted.</p>

<p>This is a brand new feature to FreeMathHelp.com -- give it a whirl and s=
ee what you think!</p>

<div class=3D"examples">
    <h3>Try factoring:</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>x^2 + 5x + 6</li>
        <li>x^2 - 9</li>
        <li>2x^2 + 7x + 3</li>
        <li>x^3 - 8</li>
        <li>x^2 - 4x + 4</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<h3>Common Factoring Questions</h3>
<p>Here are some questions other visitors have asked on our free <a href=3D=
"https://www.freemathhelp.com/forum/">math help message board</a>. Perhaps =
you can learn from the questions someone else has already asked.</p>
<ul>
    <li><a href=3D"https://www.freemathhelp.com/forum/threads/90151-How-can=
-i-factor-f(x)-2x-2-x-6">How can i factor f(x) =3D 2x^2 + x - 6</a></li>
    <li><a href=3D"https://www.freemathhelp.com/forum/threads/79098-challen=
ge-question-Factor-the-polynomial-completely">challenge question -- Factor =
the polynomial completely</a></li>
    <li><a href=3D"https://www.freemathhelp.com/forum/threads/83807-How-to-=
factor-this-expression">How to factor this expression?</a></li>
    <li><a href=3D"https://www.freemathhelp.com/forum/threads/71754-I-forgo=
t-how-to-factor!-I-don-t-know-where-to-start">I forgot how to factor! I don=
't know where to start...</a></li>
    <li><a href=3D"https://www.freemathhelp.com/forum/threads/82519-How-to-=
factor-these-equations-TRY-IT-NOT-AS-EASY-AS-IT-SOUNDS!">How to factor thes=
e equations?</a></li>
</ul>

<h3>Final Thoughts</h3>
<p>You may want to <a href=3D"https://www.freemathhelp.com/quadratic-formul=
a/">read up</a> on the quadratic formula to help your algebra knowledge rat=
her than relying on this solver. Afterall, the point is to learn the concep=
t, not just get the answer... right?</p>
<p> Also, while this calculator page is tailored for algebraic expressions,=
 you might be looking to solve for the prime factorization of a number. For=
 example, finding all the prime numbers that divide into 56 (7 and 2). We a=
lso have a page on the <a href=3D"https://www.freemathhelp.com/greatest-com=
mon-factor/">greatest common factor</a> and a link for <a href=3D"http://ww=
w.coolmath.com/prealgebra/01-gcfs-lcms/04-least-common-multiples-01">least =
common multiple</a> available.</p>


